# Version 1.0.0

Initial release.

## Added

- Initial NeoForge 1.21.1 support.
- Veil shader capture and Iris shader-program translation.
- Vertex and fragment shader integration into Iris G-buffer programs.
- Opaque Veil effect support.
- Translucent Veil effect support through `EntitiesTrans`.
- Dithering fallback for translucent effects.
- Iris shadow-pass integration for Veil-rendered geometry.
- Shader cache with automatic invalidation after shaderpack reloads.
- Graceful fallback to standard Veil rendering when Iris shaders are disabled.
- Bundled GLSL Transformer runtime.

===============================================================================

# Version 1.1.0

Dynamic Veil lighting support and rendering controls.

## Added

- Dedicated Iris-compatible fullscreen light pass.
- Veil point-light support with shaderpacks enabled.
- Veil area- and cone-light support with shaderpacks enabled.
- Multiple-light color accumulation and color mixing.
- Perceptual RGB luminance normalization.
- Configurable exposure, color strength, neutral brightness, and luminance boost.
- Configurable color saturation with a slightly richer default.
- In-game configuration screen with live updates.
- Default `O` key binding and mod-list configuration entry.
- Persistent JSON configuration.
- F3 diagnostics for pass state, light counts, voxel occlusion, and render settings.
- World-position reconstruction from the Iris depth buffer.
- Screen-space surface-normal reconstruction.
- Angle-dependent diffuse surface lighting.
- Veil voxel-grid integration for occluded lights.
- DDA-based block shadow calculation.
- Leaves as voxel shadow casters.
- Partial light transmission through leaves.

## Improved

- More consistent brightness between red, green, and blue lights.
- More natural surface response based on the angle toward each light.
- Smooth grazing-angle lighting without a hard Lambert cutoff.
- Texture preservation under bright and overlapping colored lights.
- Continuous color mixing without dominant-channel seams.
- Color-neutral intensity compression for smooth RGB transitions.
- Brighter shaderpack lighting with additional tone-map headroom.
- Expanded exposure and color-strength adjustment ranges.
- Stabilized reconstructed surface normals to remove view-dependent striping on flat surfaces.
- Gamut-safe saturation adjustment without hard channel clipping.
- Recentered the configuration layout with consistent title, hint, slider, and button spacing.
- Reduced unnecessary DDA work outside a light's range or on unlit surfaces.
- Light-block self-occlusion handling.

## Fixed

- Fixed Veil lights disappearing when shaderpacks were enabled.
- Fixed light colors appearing mostly white.
- Fixed light influence moving with the camera or cursor.
- Fixed harsh color transitions between differently colored lights.
- Fixed overexposed areas losing their visible texture.
- Fixed occluded Light Blocks appearing disabled while the camera was nearby.
- Fixed leaves failing to cast voxel shadows.
- Replaced direct client-memory voxel uploads with persistent pixel-buffer
  staging to avoid the NVIDIA driver crashes observed during voxel-grid updates.

===============================================================================

# Version 1.2.0

Performance, stability, color balancing, and integration improvements.

## Added

- Performance, Balanced, and High rendering-quality presets.
- Live quality selection in the in-game configuration screen.
- `#veil_iris_lights:non_occluding` block tag for light-source blocks that
  should not block their own Veil light.
- Public `VeilIrisLightOcclusion` registration API for client mods.
- Optional built-in tag entry for `yesmenn:colored_light`.

## Improved

- Reduced the blue-channel brightness advantage with bounded, smooth luminance
  compensation for more even RGB falloff and better-centered color mixing.
- Cached all fullscreen light-pass uniform locations.
- Reused light upload arrays and shadow normal matrices instead of allocating
  them repeatedly while rendering.
- Avoided repeated framebuffer completeness checks when the render target has
  not changed.
- Restored OpenGL texture bindings per texture unit after the light pass.
- Added a lower-cost derivative-normal path for Performance and Balanced modes.
- Reduced normal-depth sampling and disabled voxel tracing in Performance mode.
- Kept all quality presets at the full 48 point-light and 16 area-light limits.
- Dropped stale translated-shader cache references whenever Iris rebuilds its
  shaderpack pipeline while leaving OpenGL resource ownership to Iris.
- Simplified the translucent dithering patcher and removed unused code paths.
- Reduced routine shader translation messages from info to debug logging.
- Replaced the hard-coded MennURL light-block check with a reusable block tag.

## Fixed

- Fixed stale translated shader references accumulating across shaderpack reloads.
- Fixed a native crash during shaderpack switching caused by closing
  Iris-owned shader programs from the Compat cache.
- Fixed invalid Veil development-resource watch paths spamming startup errors.
- Fixed the active texture unit not always being restored correctly after the
  shaderpack light pass.
- Fixed excessive blue luminance compensation producing a visibly larger blue
  falloff and shifting cyan transitions toward green.
- Restored Veil's camera-centered voxel shadow grid so visible walls and
  surfaces receive consistent occlusion from all nearby light sources.
- Traced distant light rays through the known section of the voxel grid without
  abruptly suppressing lights outside its finite range.
- Kept the existing multiplicative shaderpack light compositing to avoid
  over-brightening shaderpack output.
- Kept lights visible without temporary occlusion only while Veil is actively
  rebuilding its voxel shadow grid.
